who: Valentine Michael Smith, the orphaned child of Earth's first Mars expedition, raised by the Old Ones of Mars and returned to a humanity he must learn from the ground up.
what: The human stranger who is more Martian than man — heir to a fortune and a planet, who becomes a messiah and founds the Church of All Worlds.
why: To share the water of life — to teach humankind to grok, to love without fear, to dissolve the walls between self and other until "thou art God."
how: By discipline of mind learned on Mars — telekinesis, control of his body, the slow full understanding called grokking — and by giving himself, in the end, to the crowd that destroyed him.
where: Born on Mars, raised among the Old Ones, returned to a wary Earth, and at last to a faith that outlives his body.
